Plot of data collected in 2002-2003 on selectivity of fish predation on infected Daphnia

Raw data are available in photocopies of lab notebooks. Data used in this file are taken from a Systat file that was originally created back when first analyzed data (e.g., for Duffy et al. 2005 L&O and for Duffy & Hall 2008 AmNat)

fish <- read.csv("FishSummary20022003_forR.csv", na.strings = "?")

metschplot <- fish %>%
  filter(Comparison ==c("Metsch")) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Infected,y=Alpha,fill=Host,shape=Lake)) +
  geom_point() +
  ylab("Chesson's alpha") +
  theme_bw()

metschplot

fullplot <- fish %>%
  filter(Infected ==c("Infected")) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Parasite,y=Alpha,colour=Host,shape=Lake)) +
  scale_colour_manual(values=c("black","gray")) +
  geom_point(size=4) +
  ylab("Chesson's alpha") +
  scale_y_continuous(limits=c(0.5,1.0)) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0.5, linetype="dotted") 

fullplot

save_plot("fullplot.jpg", fullplot, base_height=4, base_width = 6)

metschsporeplot <- spore %>%
  filter(Parasite==c("Metsch")) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Source,y=sporesperdaphnia)) +
  geom_point(size=4,position=position_jitter(w=0.3, h = 0.0)) +
  ylab("Spores per Daphnia") +
  ggtitle("Metschnikowia")

pastsporeplot <- spore %>%
  filter(Parasite==c("Pasteuria")) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Source,y=sporesperdaphnia)) +
  geom_point(size=4) +
  ylab("Spores per Daphnia") +
  ggtitle("Pasteuria")

combinedplot <- ggdraw() +
  draw_plot(metschsporeplot,0,0,0.6,1.0) +
  draw_plot(pastsporeplot,0.6,0,0.4,1.0) 

combinedplot

save_plot("combinedplot.jpg", combinedplot)
metschsporeboxplot <- spore %>%
  filter(Parasite==c("Metsch")) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Source,y=sporesperdaphnia)) +

  ggtitle("Pasteuria")

combinedboxplot <- ggdraw() +

combinedboxplot

Finally, make a plot showing the infectivity of the spores retrieved from fish fecal pellets

inf <- read.csv("FishGutPassageInfectivitySummary20042012.csv", na.strings = "?")
head(inf)

## 1 2004      KBS   Metsch   Control   1  0.8333333
## 2 2004      KBS   Metsch   Control   2  0.8666667
## 3 2004      KBS   Metsch   Control   3  1.0000000
## 4 2004      KBS   Metsch   Control   4  0.8333333
## 5 2004      KBS   Metsch   Control   5  0.7666667
## 6 2004      KBS   Metsch      Fish   1  0.8666667
colnames(inf)
## [1] "Year"       "Location"   "Parasite"   "Treatment"  "Rep"       
## [6] "AvgPropInf"
str(inf)
## 'data.frame':    41 obs. of  6 variables:
##  $ Year      : int  2004 2004 2004 2004 2004 2004 2004 2004 2004 2012 ...
##  $ Location  : Factor w/ 2 levels "GaTech","KBS": 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 1 ...
##  $ Parasite  : Factor w/ 2 levels "Metsch","Past": 1 1 1 1 1 1 1 1 1 2 ...
##  $ Treatment : Factor w/ 2 levels "Control","Fish": 1 1 1 1 1 2 2 2 2 1 ...
##  $ Rep       : Factor w/ 13 levels "1","2","3","4",..: 1 2 3 4 5 1 3 4 5 6 ...
##  $ AvgPropInf: num  0.833 0.867 1 0.833 0.767 ...
infplot <- inf %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Parasite,y=AvgPropInf,color=Treatment)) +
  scale_colour_manual(values=c("#000000","#999999")) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  ylab("Proportion infected") 

infplot

save_plot("infplot.jpg", infplot, base_height=4, base_width = 6)
